Building, installing and using a simple package consisting in a single library and an executable (named `dummy` and
`dummyc` resp.)

To build the package
- cd ./build
- make 
- make test
- make install
- make opam.install 
- make opam.show (checks that a package with name "dummy" is not already installed) 

To use the package
- cd ../use
- make doc.view
- make 

To uninstall the package
- cd ../build
- make opam.remove



